This is the README for Data::Kanji::Tomoe version 0.03.

Data::Kanji::Tomoe is a "module" for the Perl computer programming language, a
library of computer code to install on a computer.  This document contains four
sections:

1. About - what the module does

2. Documentation - how to learn more about the module

3. Installation - how to install this module on a computer

4. Help - what to do if you get stuck

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

1. ABOUT

Data::Kanji::Tomoe - parse the data files of the Tomoe project

This Perl module parses the kanji or hanzi data files supplied with
"the Tomoe "handwriting recognition engine"|/Tomoe".

The data itself is not supplied with this module.

The parsing is based on "XML::Parser". It breaks the Tomoe data into
individual characters, and calls a subroutine supplied by the user
with the data for each character.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

2. DOCUMENTATION

You can read the documentation for the module online at the following websites:

    * http://search.cpan.org/perldoc?Data::Kanji::Tomoe
    * http://metacpan.org/release/Data-Kanji-Tomoe

(These links go to the latest version of the module.)

After installing the module, you can read the documentation on your computer
using

    perldoc Data::Kanji::Tomoe

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

3. INSTALLATION

To install the module from CPAN, use

    cpan Data::Kanji::Tomoe

If you have the App::cpanminus installer, you may prefer

    cpanm Data::Kanji::Tomoe

To install the module from the source file, Data-Kanji-Tomoe-0.03.tar.gz,
follow this sequence of commands:

    tar xfz Data-Kanji-Tomoe-0.03.tar.gz
    cd Data-Kanji-Tomoe-0.03
    perl Makefile.PL
    make
    make install

If you want to test the module before installing it, use "make test" after
"make" and before "make install".

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

4. HELP

To get help with the module, you can email the author, Ben Bullock, at
<bkb@cpan.org>. If you think there is a problem in the module, you can report a
bug at 

<https://github.com/benkasminbullock/Data-Kanji-Tomoe/issues>,

or if you want to alter the source code of Data::Kanji::Tomoe, try the public
repository on github at 

<https://github.com/benkasminbullock/Data-Kanji-Tomoe>. 

